# Normalize all text files to LF in the repository and on checkout.
#
# Why: the engine's parsers and the doc pipeline assume LF line endings. On
# Windows with core.autocrlf=true a checkout/clone rewrites the working tree to
# CRLF, which (before the parser CRLF-normalization fixes) silently broke
# proposal section/chart parsing and produced spurious "modified" churn. Pinning
# eol=lf keeps the working tree LF everywhere, regardless of a contributor's
# core.autocrlf setting — a permanent guard on top of the code-level fix.
# Shell scripts (doctor.sh, share.sh) also REQUIRE LF to run.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary files — never normalize.
*.png  binary
*.jpg  binary
*.jpeg binary
*.gif  binary
*.ico  binary
*.pdf  binary
*.woff  binary
*.woff2 binary
*.ttf  binary
*.otf  binary
